SIMPLE: misfortune
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Misfortune
<hw>Mis*for"tune</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Bad fortune or
luck; calamity; an evil accident; disaster; mishap; mischance.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Consider why the change was wrought,⟦br⟧
You 'll find his <qex>misfortune</qex>, not his fault.</q>
<rj><qau>Addison.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><syn><b>Syn.</b> -- Calamity; mishap; mischance; misadventure; ill;
harm; disaster. See <er>Calamity</er>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Misfortune</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Misfortune
<hw>Mis*for"tune</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To happen unluckily or
unfortunately; to miscarry; to fail.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Stow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Misfortuned</ent>⟦br⟧
